> **Status: FROZEN 2026-05-19 pre-measurement.** Per `CAMPAIGN_DISCIPLINE.md` Rule 1.1, binding. No amendments are permitted post-measurement; pre-measurement amendments are permitted only if flagged explicitly and made before any computation is admitted.

## 0. Strategic role

Gate 3 is the **cheap global kill-switch** of the MCG (M ⊕ C ⊕ G) gate campaign, pulled to the front (out of dependency order) deliberately. A negative result here makes Gates 0/1/2/4 and the entire unification campaign moot. Highest expected-value single experiment available pre-campaign.

The hypothesis Gate 3 tests is structural, not numerical: **does the G-candidate observable (σ1 exponent) carry a signal that survives subtraction of the substrate-mandated component M, or is σ1 = 1.000 substrate-universality masquerade?**

A HALT here means the architecture's G term was an artifact of substrate structure (BACL-mandated lattice content) for this fixture, and the architecture must be reassessed before any further gates are funded. A GREEN means G is plausibly real post-decomposition and Gate 0 proceeds.

