- Subnormal-regime behaviour of `f_float` (this fixture stays at `f_float ≥ ~2^(−40)`, far above the `2^(−1021)` c2 floor).
- Other rounding modes (round-to-nearest-even only).
- Other formats (binary64 only).
- Conical compatibility singularity fixture (the alternative Gate 3 fixture; not used here — Schwarzschild chosen because c2 theorem applies most directly).
- Re-running Gate 3 with a different interpretation of M-subtraction (the decision arm is interpretation (3) only; interpretations (1) and (2) are not eligible substitutes per §3).
- Any non-decision use of interpretation (2). Per user direction, interpretation (2) is a Gate 2 / G-characterization instrument and is excluded from Gate 3.

